    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>[You are in the body of a castoff named Endira Thirdloss, a caretaker of an ancient tower. A construct hovers next to you, informing you that your commander, the First, is trying to enter the tower. Unfortunately, it has been so long since anybody entered the tower, that even the construct no longer remembers how to activate the portal.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Figure out how to open the portal.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Dick around.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Let me out of this Mere already.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>[You do so. It's not that hard â€” this is a placeholder.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>[You do so. While you are dicking around, you accidentally open the portal anyway... because this is placeholder.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
